#this file can't contain anything that .gitignore doesn't contain since otherwise git will report the tree as dirty during docker builds!
#this would be bad for dynamic version generation. (e.g. setuptools-scm would then report the version as a dev version)
#the final docker container won't contain the source code anyway, so there is no downside in having nothing in here anyway
#we just include dirs that can get very large to reduce size of context that needs to be copied
**/__pycache__/
**/pypackages/
**/.venv/
**/node_modules/
**/build/
**/dist/
**/project-W-data/
**.log
**/.DS_Store
